definition.value: Combining with the peptide apelin to initiate a change in cell activity.
The process in which a cell switches cell cycle mode.
Either of two different areas at opposite ends of an axis of a cell.
A clathrin-sculpted lipid bilayer membrane-enclosed vesicle after clathrin release.
A clathrin-sculpted lipid bilayer membrane-enclosed vesicle after clathrin release and containing glutamate.
A clathrin-sculpted lipid bilayer membrane-enclosed vesicle after clathrin release and containing acetylcholine.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of the clathrin-sculpted acetylcholine transport vesicle.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of the clathrin-sculpted glutamate transport vesicle.
The volume enclosed by the membrane of a cytoplasmic membrane-bounded vesicle.
Increases the activity of phosphatidylcholine-sterol O-acyltransferase, an enzyme that converts cholesterol and phosphatidylcholine (lecithins) to cholesteryl esters and lyso-phosphatidylcholines.
Increases the activity of a lipase, an enzyme that catalyzes of the hydrolysis of a lipid.
Increases the activity of a lipoprotein lipase, an enzyme that catalyzes of the hydrolysis of a lipid within a lipoprotein.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the microtubule spindle during a mitotic cell cycle.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a lysozyme, an enzyme that hydrolyses the beta- (1,4) glycosidic bond between N-acetylmuramic acid and N-acetylglucosamine in peptidoglycan.

label.value: negative regulation of cell proliferation involved in contact inhibition

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of cell proliferation in response to cell density.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glial cell proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of glial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of glial cell proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of glial cell proliferation

definition.value: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of glial cell proliferation.
Differentiated cytoplasm associated with a pole of an oocyte, egg or early embryo that will be inherited by the cells that will give rise to the germ line.

Modulates the activity of GTP cyclohydrolase I. GTP cyclohydrolase I activity catalyzes the reaction -  GTP + 2 H2O -eq- formate + 2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-(erythro-1,2,3-trihydroxypropyl)-dihydropteridine triphosphate.

The membrane surrounding the outer segment of a vertebrate photoreceptor. The photoreceptor inner segment contains mitochondria, ribosomes and membranes where opsin molecules are assembled and passed to be part of the outer segment discs.
A structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg. The fertilization envelope forms from the vitelline membrane after fertilization as a result of cortical granule release.
A glycoprotein-based structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg before fertilization.
The cytoplasmic part that serves as a nutrient reserve or energy source for the developing embryo.
Discrete structures that partition the water-soluble portion of the yolk of oocytes and ova, which may or may not be membrane enclosed.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a peptidyl-dipeptidase. Peptidyl-dipeptidase activity catalyzes the release of C-terminal dipeptides from a polypeptide chain.

label.value: activation of meiosis involved in egg activation

definition.value: Any process that starts the inactive process of meiosis in an egg after the egg has been fertilized or physiologically activated. Eggs generally arrest in meiosis and complete the process after activation.
A secretory vesicle that is stored under the cell membrane of an egg. These vesicles fuse with the egg plasma membrane as part of egg activation and are part of the block to polyspermy.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate or frequency of epithelial cell proliferation that results in the lung attaining its shape.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the lung.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung bud dilation

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate or frequency of epithelial cell proliferation that results in the lung bud increasing in size radially.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung bud dilation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells that contribute to the radial growth of a lung bud.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in prostatic bud elongation

definition.value: The multiplication of epithelial cells, contributing to the expansion of the primary prostatic bud.

label.value: negative regulation of mitotic anaphase-promoting complex activity

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate frequency or extent of anaphase-promoting complex activity regulating mitotic cell cycle transitions.

label.value: inhibition of mitotic anaphase-promoting complex activity

definition.value: Any process that prevents the activation of anaphase-promoting complex activity regulating the mitotic cell cycle.
Modulates the rate of NTP hydrolysis by a NTPase.
Modulates the rate of ATP hydrolysis by an ATPase.

label.value: regulation of ascospore wall beta-glucan biosynthetic process

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of ascospore wall beta-glucan biosynthetic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of beta-glucans, compounds composed of glucose residues linked by beta-D-glucosidic bonds, found in the walls of ascospores.

label.value: regulation of ascospore wall (1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucan biosynthetic process

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of ascospore wall (1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucan biosynthetic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of (1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucans, compounds composed of glucose residues linked by (1--gt-3)-beta-D--glucosidic bonds, found in the walls of ascospores.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of homologous chromosome segregation, the cell cycle process in which replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the first division of the meiotic cell cycle. Each replicated chromosome, composed of two sister chromatids, aligns at the cell equator, paired with its homologous partner -  this pairing off, referred to as synapsis, permits genetic recombination. One homolog (both sister chromatids) of each morphologic type goes into each of the resulting chromosome sets.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of meiosis I, a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the first phase of meiosis, in which cells divide and homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two daughter cells.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland bud elongation

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mammary gland bud epithelial cells, resulting in the elongation of the bud.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland bud elongation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mammary gland bud epithelial cell proliferation that results in the elongation of the bud.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

definition.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells of the submandibular salivary gland, resulting in the expansion of a cell population and the shaping of the gland.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an endoribonuclease, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of ester linkages within ribonucleic acid by creating internal breaks.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of deoxyribonuclease.
The multiplication or reproduction of spongiotrophoblast cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the spongiotrophoblast layer.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of spongiotrophoblast cell proliferation.
